pageContext.description: $ raised ribs on faces, well marked. Edge blunt,\& broken. Socketed squarish with angles rounded. Loop perfectly preserved, smooth and glossy. Ridges of juncture down sides. Deep purple & green staining inside lower part of socket.
pageContext.patina: olive to grey-green, lustrous; red-brown near on face of edge;patches broken through to blue-green core.
pageContext.surface: well preserved in parts; sides partially coated with red-brown sandy corrosion; in patches elsewhere.
pageContext.other: Weight given as 8.25 ounces - I have converted to grams
pageContext.associations: Note preserved with this implement: "This is an ancient Roman Celt, whereof 3 were found in the year 1779 in the grounds of Nicholas Skyleman of Snettisham in the County of Norfolk, Esq., one of which was presented to the British Museum, another he kept for himself, & this third he gave to my father who set a great antiquarian value on the same" (Sgd.) H. BANKS,, Whixley (W.R.Yorks) 17 Sept. 1840. Addressed to T. C. Banks esq., 15 Edwards Square, Kensington (Sir Thomas Christopher banks, 1765-1854)
pageContext.collection: Private,W.J. Hemp Esq. F.S.A.,Minshall, High Wycombe, Bucks,Drawn 11th Oct 1928 L.F.C.
